org.webchecker.search

Interface Parasite


  • public interface Parasite
    Class representing getting results from searching engine, we are parasitizing on. If we want to do this kind of parasitizing, we have to get a source document and to extract results from it. This is why there are functions url(String) and extractResults(org.jsoup.nodes.Document).

    We can say, that the url(String) is a help function for generating URL from query. This can be helpful when searching a lot.

    Version:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • url

        java.lang.String url(java.lang.String query)
        This method should return an URL from given query. We have to be able to download a web page with search results from the URL returned by this method.
        Parameters:
        query - the query to be searched with the engine, this parasite is parasitizing on
        Returns:
        URL from which can we download the web page with search results

      • extractResults

        Results extractResults(org.jsoup.nodes.Document doc)
        Extract search results from given document and create new Results object with it.
        Parameters:
        doc - document to extract results from
        Returns:
        results extracted from given document

      • anotherURL

        default Parasite anotherURL(java.lang.String url)
        Returns new parasite with same extractResults(org.jsoup.nodes.Document) but redefined url(String) method. The new url(String) method will be returning given string.
        Parameters:
        url - new returning value, that should new url(String) method return
        Returns:
        new parasite with redefined url(String) method

      • search

        default Results search(java.lang.String query,
                       int timeout)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Returns results from searching the given query with the engine.
        Parameters:
        query - the query to be searched with the engine. If null, the behavior will depend on url(String) method behavior
